<descript>
<abstract>A three-foot cell size Digital Elevation Model raster was created from the ground classified LIDAR points plus the breaklines. The files are delivered in 3,000ft by 3,000ft tiles, The rasters are delivered in .img file format.</abstract>
<purpose>LiDAR terrain mapping to the Colorado Water Conservation Board (CWCB) for all or portions of Garfield, Eagle, Summit,
Clear Creek, Gilpin, Douglas and Jefferson Counties. Approximately 6,150 square miles.</purpose>
</descript>
